column5: When it comes to a historic building.. with a roof and wall that they couldn't figure out how to shore and replace over the last numerous months... and still save the facade... it was a pretty easy conclusion to make...  like I've said before.. I've been underneath one of these old buildings that came down while working in Cabbagetown in the late 70's and if we we're smart we would have burned that bugger down before it almost killed me and 5 other works.
Yeah And I Also Agree It Was An Inside Job. Its going to be replaced with a condo
